    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>\u00a0</p>\n<p>Shivam is very weak at mathematics. His friend Chirag who is extremely good at mathematics gives him a mathematics problem just to make fun of him because Chirag loves to humiliate him in public. The problem is as follows:\n\nGiven the number of terms <b>n</b> and the last element <b>k</b> of the strictly increasing Arithmetic Progression(A.P), you have to print the first term of the Arithmetic Progression such that the common difference is odd and the sum of any two terms in the series in not present in the series. Also, the difference between the last term and first term is minimum.\n\nSince you are Shivam's best friend please help him to find a solution to this problem.</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n\n\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>The first line of the input contains an integer <b>T</b> denoting the number of test cases.\nThe first line of each test case contains two numbers <b>n</b> (no of terms) and <b>k</b> (the last term).</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>For every testcase print the first term of the Arithmetic Progression on new line..</p>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>t</b> \u2264 <b>10</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>n</b> \u2264 <b>10<sup>12</sup></b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>k</b> \u2264 <b>10<sup>12</sup></b></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n2\n1 5\n2 5\n\n<b>Output:</b>\n5\n4\n</pre>\n<p>\u00a0</p>\n",
